msgstr ""

#: ../../storage.rst:41 a1ead576fde948ff8391fe685ffc4698
msgid ""
"In certain instances, you may encounter challenges utilizing the primary "
"disk for log storage, as the user interface may not present any options. "
"In such cases, the issue typically stems from a pre-existing partition on"
" the disk, which must be removed beforehand to ensure proper utilization "
"by the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../storage.rst:44 22ccbbab03f04cb0a04c2cf827567bf5
msgid ""
"This typically occurs even after performing a default reset using "
"failsafe mode (which does not remove the log partition), in order to "
"allow the system to use again the storage to save new logs you need to "
"remove the old partition."
